			  			<HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  			I have noticed AS is somewhat unbalanced and the game is more about who you know then how good you are. The more you know, the &quot;better&quot; you are. Then again perhaps the developers intended on this game being this way.<br />
<br />
I think the 50-200% range rule is ridiculous. It just seems that no matter how well you prep your fleets someone 2x your size will most likely kick your butt. Detection also makes the game even more unbalanced. You could have your entire fleet wiped out before they can even fire a shot. Shouldn't it be simultaneous volleys? Realistically when two armadas meet both sides should have at least a chance to fire? So basically you could have the more superior fleet and still lose to an inferior.<br />
<br />
Protection only comes when you take 60% damage? Ugh...<br />
<br />
I really like the idea of 70-200% ranges. It would make the game some what more fair and takes a lot more skill than sheer brute force. Imagine you are 70k and can only be attacked by someone 100k your power....instead of 140k. 30-45% damage before protection also seems like it would help balance the game some.<br />
<br />
Just some thoughts.<br />
						<P align=right> </P>
					</TD>
